# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __complex__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__complex__')
#
# decimal.Decimal does NOT define __complex__ in its own __dict__: false.
# __complex__ signals support for complex() conversion. Decimal is not a
# complex numeric type and does not implement __complex__; complex() on a
# Decimal is not directly supported via this dunder method.
# All other decimal classes: false.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

