# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __int__, __float__, __complex__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# decimal.Decimal: __int__ = true (int(Decimal('3')) supported via __int__),
# __float__ = true (float(Decimal('3.14')) supported via __float__),
# __complex__ = false (Decimal does not define __complex__; complex() is not
# directly supported on Decimal via this dunder method).
# This true/true/false pattern is the key finding of wave 673 for the decimal
# module: Decimal supports integer and float conversion but is not a complex
# numeric type and does not define __complex__.
# All other decimal classes (Context, DecimalException, InvalidOperation,
# Overflow, Underflow): false for all three operators.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

